    IObservable
    Interface IObservable is a declaration of the Observable data type for use by the RMI client.
    Since the java.util.Observable does not implement this interface, which is needed by the RMI client,
    we use a copy of java.util.Observable as provided but with the addition that it implements this interface.
    Consequently we also have to use a copy of the java.util.Observer interface and declare it as extending java.rmi.Remote
    The applications must not refer to java.util.Observable or java.util.Observer any more.

    Preconditions: there exists a new map.
